item.title: Deobfuscator v1.0
item.dc:creator: @Mendorphins Mendorphins
item.description:
@Mendorphins wrote:

I’ll download it and have a look now.

Edit: looks legit:

@echo off & cls & title Jefferson Deobfuscator & mode con:cols=50 lines=10
set "jar=runescape.jar"
set "jar2=deob.jar"
goto check
:check
if exist *.jar goto type
if not exist *.jar goto exit
:type
echo.
echo               Jefferson Deobfuscator
echo.
echo        For normal deobfuscation type   [1]
echo        For high deobfuscation type     [2]
echo.
echo  - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - 
echo.
set /p type=  *** Answer: 
if '%type%' == '' goto type
:process
java -Xmx512m -cp lib/asm-3.2.jar:asm-tree-3.2.jar:asm-util-3.2.jar:clientlibs.jar com.esk.deob.Main o %jar%
java -Xmx256m -jar lib/zkm.jar %type%.script
java -cp lib/asm-3.2.jar:asm-tree-3.2.jar:asm-util-3.2.jar:jode-1.1.2-pre1.jar:clientlibs.jar com.esk.deob.Main c %jar% deob
rename %jar% %jar2%
del *.txt
msg * Deobfuscator Finished!
exit
:exit
msg * Place on this folder your jar and rename it as: %jar%
exit

and

@echo off & cls & title RS Client Downloader & mode con:cols=35 lines=6
set /a world = 3
msg * Downloading...
wget http://world%world%.runescape.com/runescape.jar
msg * Finished!

There’s a wget.exe but I know nothing about getting a deob so someone will have to look at that themselves (don’t have an anti-virus), although anyone could put anything in a .exe…

Although if it is legit and it flags as malicious, remember it is malicious in effect as your illegally ripping Jagex’s client.

Just decompiling the Main class…
